ants-terminal (0.6.33-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Root-cause fix for the long tail of "Review Changes button does
    nothing" reports: a 0.6.26 focusChanged lambda was queuing a
    singleShot(0) refocus that could fire between a button's
    mousePress and mouseRelease, ripping focus off the button
    mid-click and silently cancelling clicked(). The lambda now
    exempts QAbstractButton focus targets and defers while a mouse
    button is held down.
  * Status-bar chips converted to plain QLabel / QPushButton with
    QSizePolicy::Fixed. Only the transient notification slot is
    elastic and elides. Retires the ElidedLabel + stylesheet
    chip-padding class of bug (branch chip truncating to "..." with
    ample room). Branch chip colour moved from green to cyan so it
    is visually distinct from Claude-state chips.
  * Review Changes button is now tri-state: hidden outside git
    repos, disabled when clean and in-sync, enabled otherwise.
    Probe switched to `git status --porcelain=v1 -b` so unpushed
    commits count as reviewable work. Global QPushButton:hover rule
    now :enabled-gated. Dialog is fully async — opens with a
    placeholder and streams git output in, renders Status + Unpushed
    + Diff sections.
  * Frozen-view scrollback snapshot: while scrolled up, cellAtGlobal
    / combiningAt read from a snapshot of the screen at scroll-up
    time, not the live grid. Locked by
    tests/features/scrollback_frozen_view/.
  * One-click "Install Claude Code status-bar hooks" action in
    Settings > General writes ~/.config/ants-terminal/hooks/
    claude-forward.sh and idempotently merges PreToolUse /
    PostToolUse / Stop / PreCompact / SessionStart entries into
    ~/.claude/settings.json.
  * Richer Claude status vocabulary (idle / thinking / bash /
    reading / editing / searching / browsing / planning / auditing
    / prompting / compacting) with plan-mode and /audit detection
    in the transcript parser; new planModeChanged and
    auditingChanged signals; refreshStatusBarForActiveTab() as the
    single per-tab refresh entry point.
  * Fixed scrollback blank-line bloat on inactive tabs after
    session restart — recalcGridSize ran on unlaid-out tabs and
    shrank grids to 3x10 (pre-layout guard added), and
    TerminalGrid::resize pushed every reflowed row to scrollback
    (now skips entirely-blank rows).
  * Fixed tab colours not persisting across restarts — UUID-keyed
    tab_groups only worked with session persistence enabled; new
    ordered tab_color_sequence fallback applied at startup.
  * Add-to-Allowlist button gains a 3-scan debounce against
    TUI-repaint flicker and a shared toolFinished / sessionStopped
    retraction path across scroll-scan and hook detections.
  * New config keys: notification_timeout_ms (default 5000) with a
    seconds spinner in Settings > General, and tab_color_sequence.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 18:21:22 +0200

ants-terminal (0.6.32-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Audit self-learning layer: new RuleQualityTracker
    (src/auditrulequality.{h,cpp}) records every per-rule fire and
    user-suppression event from the project Audit dialog into
    <project>/audit_rule_quality.json. 90-day rolling window, capped
    at 50 000 records per category; saves on dialog destruction and
    force-flushes on each suppression.
  * New "📊 Rule Quality" button in the audit dialog opens a modal
    per-rule stats table: 30-day fires, 30-day suppressions, FP rate
    (capped 0-100%), all-time fires, and a proposed dropIfContains
    tightening when the LCS suggester has enough samples. Sorted by
    FP rate desc so the noisiest rules surface first.
  * LCS-based tightening suggester: longest common substring across
    the last 5 suppressed line texts per rule. Floor at 6 chars and
    at least one structural boundary character (space, paren, brace,
    bracket, semicolon, quote, angle bracket) so the suggester
    proposes rule-shape filters, not project-noun filters.
  * New docs/RECOMMENDED_ROUTINES.md captures the four Claude Code
    routines that earn a slot on the shared account quota — nightly
    audit triage, PR security review, weekly audit-rule self-triage,
    monthly ROADMAP-item scoper.
  * CI build hotfix for 0.6.31: QMessageAuthenticationCode::addData
    on older Qt 6.x does not accept QByteArrayView; switched the
    OSC 133 verifier to the (const char*, qsizetype) overload.
    Behaviour unchanged.

 -- Anthony Schemel <aant.schemel@gmail.com>  Sat, 18 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0000

ants-terminal (0.6.31-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: OSC 133 HMAC-signed shell integration. When
    $ANTS_OSC133_KEY is set, every OSC 133 marker (A/B/C/D) must carry
    a matching HMAC-SHA256 tag; forged markers from in-terminal
    processes are dropped and surface a throttled "OSC 133 forgery
    detected" status-bar warning. When the key is unset, behaviour is
    unchanged from 0.6.30. Shell hooks ship under
    /usr/share/ants-terminal/shell-integration/{bash,zsh}.
  * Review Changes status-bar button no longer silently swallows
    clicks on a clean repo — the disabled-but-visible state was
    advertising itself as actionable via the global hover stylesheet
    while QAbstractButton dropped the press. Button is now hidden on
    clean repos and reappears when a real diff exists.
  * Shift+Enter no longer wedges the tab in bracketed-paste mode
    (0.6.26 regression). QByteArray(literal, 8) truncated the 13-byte
    paste sequence and dropped the [201~ end-paste marker; switched to
    QByteArrayLiteral so the size is compile-time derived.
  * Status-bar allowlist button dedup now uses QWidget* for parity
    with the other dedup sites — fixes a stack-up when a scroll-scan
    detection fires while a hook-path container is already visible.
  * Audit signal-to-noise overhaul: two-pass triage of the Ants and
    Vestige audit runs cuts the false-positive rate from ~97% to
    under 10% with no loss of real coverage (memory_patterns,
    secrets_scan, file_perms, header_guards rule tightenings; clazy
    qt-keywords dropped; six rules gain context-window suppressions;
    tool timeouts demoted to Info).

