ants-terminal (0.6.24-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Status-bar "Add to allowlist" button now persists for the full life
    of the Claude Code permission prompt (was retracted mid-prompt by
    the TUI's own repaint traffic).
  * "Review Changes" disabled state legible on every theme, including
    One Dark and Kanagawa where the previous textSecondary-based fix
    still failed WCAG AA.
  * Extend the main-screen scrollback-doubling suppression window to
    cover `CSI H; CSI 0J` and corner-cursor `CSI 1J` in addition to
    `CSI 2J`. All three sequences produce the same post-state (every
    visible cell cleared) and therefore triggered the same
    scrollback-doubling bug under TUI repaint bursts.

